nk, from the context of many things He said, that He wanted us to live our lives as if it is how we live today...this day...in the now...is what matters to our salvation.  <br><br>Whether our theology is that we are saved once and on our way to heaven, saved daily, or saved when we get to the end, we can all be assured that we were, are and will be saved if we remain as close as possible to Jesus, in word and deed, every day, especially this day.   <br><br>Thanks for the response and feel free to differ with me anytime. Iron sharpens iron and I love a chance to learn and grow.</span>
