        June 8, 2009<br><br>We kind of protested from them<img src="/images/biggrin.png" border="0" alt="Big Grin" title="Big Grin">!<br><br>The only way we are sure of our salvation is through faith in God’s word that says;<br><br><font face="Comic Sans MS">This is my blood of the covenant, which is poured out for many for the forgiveness of sins.</font> <b>Matthew 26:28</b><br><br>Through the blood of Jesus the sins of  those who repent are forgiven, I think that we as believers of Christ should always believe in his words without question, I believe we don’t have a reason to be picky or choosy on what to believe or not as long as it is his Word. I do not think that the protestant way of asking for forgiveness is one sided based on these verses;<br><font face="Comic Sans MS">&quot;Do not judge, and you will not be judged. Do not condemn, and you will not be condemned. Forgive, and you will be forgiven.</font><b> Luke 6:37. </b><br>Firstly, we should as Christian’s have confidence that as we forgive we are bound to be forgiven, it is sort of reciprocal and not one sided for once we know that we are unable to forgive then we automatically must understand that we will not be forgiven. Secondly, those who are the true disciples of Jesus must be under the guidance or rather be filled by the Spirit of God and which through God always convinces us that we are truly forgiven;<br><font face="Comic Sans MS">But the Counselor, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, will teach you all things and will remind you of everything I have said to you.</font><b> John 14:26</b><br>Thirdly all those that are in Christ have full assurance and suffer no condemnation personal or otherwise;<br><font face="Comic Sans MS">Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus, because through Christ Jesus the law of the Spirit of life set me free from the law of sin and death. For what the law was powerless to do in that it was weakened by the sinful nature, God did by sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful man to be a sin offering. And so he condemned sin in sinful man, in order that the righteous requirements of the law might be fully met in us, who do not live according to the sinful nature but according to the Spirit.</font><br><b>ROMANS 8: 1- 4</b>.<br>The Holy Spirit is therefore the only God given evidence of the forgiveness of sin and Christ’s only witness to forgiveness of sin and validity of salvation. I understand for the need of a physical evidence you are pointing out, but unless you fulfill the predetermined concepts of forgiveness and live within the required expectations, it will count to nothing but just a ceremony that has no positive sacred significance to you’re your spiritual person.</span>
